ial from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":76,"region":76,"country":113,"address":114,"geo":115},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":116,"lon":117},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":119,"mainLang":120,"languages":121},"Latin","la",[119],{"type":123,"bibl":124},"edition",[125],{"author":126,"date":127,"citedRange":128,"ptr":129,"ref":131,"inscriptionDate":127,"title":133,"citation":134,"uri":135},"Cultrera","1951","809, 812 fig.88",{"target":130},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/D44T3NE2",{"_":132,"target":132},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002062","L'Apollonion-Artemision di Ortigia in Siracusa","\u003Cspan>G. Cultrera, «L’Apollonion-Artemision di Ortigia in Siracusa», \u003Ci>Monumenti Antichi\u003C/i> 41 (1951): 701–860\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/D44T3NE2",{"type":137,"bibl":138},"discussion",[17],{"editor":140,"principal":143,"contributors":144,"change":148},{"_":141,"ref":142},"Jonathan Prag","#JP",{"_":141,"ref":142},[145],{"_":141,"xml:id":146,"ref":147},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":149,"when":150,"who":142},"Jonathan Prag created from publications","2026-02-25","",{"n":98,"url":99,"height":100,"width":101,"desc":102,"surfaceType":103},[],[155],"Cultrera, 1951, L'Apollonion-Artemision di Ortigia in Siracusa",[157],"D44T3NE2",[159,160,161,19,24,28,162,163,164,165,163,166,167,120],"isic002127","fragment of a latin inscription",{"_":5},"syracusae","siracusa","sicilia","sicily","museo archeologico regionale paolo orsi","latin",[],{"title":170,"body":171,"divs":172,"editions":197,"images":207,"handnote":213},"ISic002127. Fragment of a Latin inscription","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]LEP̣[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]LE.[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002127_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana: drawing of Cultrera, MAL 1951: 812 fig.88\" src=\"ISic002127_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic002127.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana: drawing of Cultrera, MAL 1951: 812 fig.88\" src=\"ISic002127-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on Cultrera's drawing\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Theoretically the final letter could also be R, but in context this implausible\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>upper part of either E or F\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The fragment is reported by Cultrera, who merely comments 'sembra del tutto insignificante', and provides the drawing without further comment. [--]Lep[--] is most likely part of a name (most obviously Lepidus, but also, e.g. names based on Asclepias). The fragment does not seem ever to have been noted or recorded since, and has so far not been located.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Cultrera 1951 809, 812 fig.88 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002062\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002062\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Latin letters of the taller narrower variety, some curvature to the strokes, very short bars to E, letters of the second/third century CE? (measurement taken from drawing)\u003C/p> Line 1  45  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[173,176,179,182,185,188,191,194],{"id":174,"html":175},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003